-- Anglo, Don Group, Sasol and Vunani May Move: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   N i c k y   S m i t h   a n d   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 2010-09-30T05:49:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/the-don-group-vunani-shares-may-move-south-african-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South
Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and
prices are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose for a
third day, adding 97.36, or 0.3 percent, to 29,069.83 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): Copper snapped a two day
advance, losing as much as 1.4 percent to $7,953 a metric ton on
the London Metal Exchange. Shares of Anglo, the diversified
mining company that makes up almost 10 percent of South Africa’s
benchmark stock index, fell 3.50 rand, or 1.2 percent, to 278
rand. Shares in larger rival  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ) dropped
1.71 rand, or 0.8 percent, to 222.01 rand.  The Don Group Ltd.  (DON SJ): The hotel group said revenue
for the 12 months through June rose to 171 million rand ($24.5
million) from 65 million rand a year earlier. Shares in the
company added 2 cents, or 8.3 percent, to 26 cents.  Harmony Gold Mining Ltd.  (HAR SJ): Africa’s third-largest
producer of the metal said a second body was recovered at its
Bambanani East shaft following a Sept. 27 rockfall. Shares in
Harmony fell 1.09 rand, or 1.4 percent, to 78.90 rand.  Sallies Ltd.  (SAL SJ): The fluorspar producer said its loss
for the 12 months through June widened to 62.6 million rand from
53.2 million rand a year earlier. The Pretoria-based company’s
shares were unchanged at 10 cents.  Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Oil declined 0.3 percent to $77.65 a
barrel in electronic trading in New York. Shares in Sasol, the
world’s biggest maker of motor fuel from coal, gained 1.70 rand,
or 0.6 percent, to 312.50 rand.  Vunani Ltd.  (VUN SJ): The financial services company has
entered negotiations that may “have a material effect” on the
company’s share price. The stock was unchanged at 8 cents.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 0.9 percent to $19.90.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) slid 0.6 percent to $46.50. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) lost 1.1 percent to $63.92. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) fell 1.5 percent to $5.23. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI US)
added 0.3 percent to $15.17. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
fell 1.2 percent to $11.41. Impala Platinum Holdings Co. (IMPUY
US) lost 0.2 percent to $25.60. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) declined 0.4
percent to $5.14. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) was little changed at
$44.82. Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TLKGY US) advanced 1 percent
to $21.20.  To contact the reporters on this story:
